GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 2
HOUSE BILL 975
Committee Substitute Favorable 4/29/25
Short Title: EMS Personnel/Allow Carry of Pepper Spray. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
April 14, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ALLOW EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICES PERSONNEL, WHILE ON
3 DUTY, TO CARRY PEPPER SPRAY OPENLY OR CONCEALED.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 131E-158 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
6 "(c) The North Carolina Office of Emergency Medical Services and the Commission shall
7 adopt rules to permit emergency medical services personnel to carry, openly or concealed, any
8 pepper spray consistent with G.S. 14-401.6(a)(7). The rules adopted may require emergency
9 medical services personnel to complete training which shall not exceed NC Basic Law
10 Enforcement Training standards in the use of pepper spray and obtain the approval of the
11 affiliated EMS provider pursuant to its policy regarding use prior to carrying pepper spray and
12 prohibit the discharge of pepper spray in the ambulance compartment during transport of the
13 patient. For purposes of this subsection, the term "pepper spray" means a chemical irritant such
14 as mace, oleoresin capsicum or pepper spray, or tear gas."
15 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
*H975-v-2*

